item.dc:creator: @Ron Ron
item.description:
@Ron wrote:

Un needed…

C:\PROGRA~1\Logitech\MOUSEW~1\SYSTEM\EM_EXEC.EXE
C:\Program Files\HP\HP Software Update\HPWuSchd2.exe
C:\Program Files\Common Files\Real\Update_OB\realsched.exe
C:\Program Files\Java\jre1.5.0_06\bin\jusched.exe
C:\Program Files\HP\Digital Imaging\bin\hpqtra08.exe
C:\Program Files\iPod\bin\iPodService.exe
C:\PROGRA~1\Logitech\MOUSEW~1\SYSTEM\EM_EXEC.EXE
C:\Program Files\Brother\ControlCenter2\brctrcen.exe
C:\Program Files\Brother\Brmfcmon\BrMfcWnd.exe

Turn off those services by going to Spybot, Mode advanced, tools, system startup, and uncheck them.

If you’re not sure about one of those processes. You can read about them in your startup and see if they aren’t needed or whatever. You can also check by going to a process list you can find here. Just press Ctrl + F and type in what service you want to look up and most of them are there. Any others that you can’t find, don’t neglect www.google.com.

Everything else looks good, but I may be wrong.

~Ron
